Defendant in custody.   
Deliver Heroin within 1,000 feet of school - Guilty plea.   Convicted.   Sentence is withheld.   Defendant is placed on probation to DOC for four (4) years, to commence upon the completion of jail sentences in 15 CF 321 and 16 CF 143.  Conditions of probation are:
1) Spend twelve (12) months in jail, under the Huber Law;
2) AODA assessment and follow through counseling;
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
4) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
5) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
6) Complete HSED/GED;
7) Maintain absolute sobriety; 
8) Pay costs of action; 
9) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
10) Submit DNA sample.   
Defendant is given credit for 84 days should probation get revoked.  
